27636991.review:
Can be made better, but it's still enjoyable...

Why i like it:
* minesweeper! {[i]+1[/i]}
* [strike]with an interesting twist.[/strike] with some interesting twists. That get revealed while progressing through, not all at once. :-bd {[i]+1[/i]}
* windowed mode. :-) {[i]+1[/i]}
* steam achievements. {[i]+1[/i]}
* small storage footprint. {[i]+0.5[/i]}

Why i am tempted to dislike it at times:
* Doesn't auto-finish when "0 remaining"... {[i]-0.5[/i]}
* No left+right click on a "completed" hint to reveal remaining [strike]nearby[/strike] cells that are obviously empty. Guess i'm too used to this esoteric mechanic from the Windows Minesweeper. :-)
- I can't detect any highlight (or shadow) of the not-yet-perfected levels! Do i have to go through all of them to get the final achievement?! :-s {[i]-1[/i]}
* No volume control for the music: it's just 100% or 0%. At least i can mute it.
* No randomization. As a programmer myself, i would expect "generate board and try to solve" is not that difficult to include. Though, TBF, Hexcells Infinite does contain a random puzzle generator.
- No "level title" to tell me which level i'm currently solving. I usually minimize (or alt+tab out of) the game, and don't remember this bit of detail when i come back to it... Also, when going to the next level, i usually lose track. Guess exiting to menu to check which level is the first one unsolved is doable... But it's annoying. {[i]-0.5[/i]}
* The "column-counter" hints can initially be easily misinterpreted to be "neighbour-counter" hints that are just placed on an invisible tile... Which might lead to mistakes! Eh, i guess it just takes a bit to get used to them. {[i]-0.5[/i]}
* [strike]The "column-counter" hints don't get highlighted when they're complete. Guess i'm too used to how Picross / Griddlers work. :-)[/strike] Oh, so i have to manually do it... AND there's a guideline too?! Why is this mentioned so late after introducing the "outside number" hints?? :-< {[i]-0.5[/i]}
* Cannot save level state... {[i]-0.5[/i]}
* Inconsistent mechanic of the "-X-" hints, when they're inside a cell or outside the board... {[i]-0.5[/i]}
- No "Exit" button. Most people don't really need it, but it still would've been nice to have.

[i]Total: +0.5... So close to not recommending. xD[/i]

Update 2017-07-01: three of the dislikes i stated above are now somewhat addressed. Maybe they were from the start and i missed them, or maybe they were implemented in the mean time. But i still believe the level number (why is this NOT the x-y combo from the menu, but a counter not shown anywhere else?!), the Quit button, and the difference between perfected and completed-with-mistakes levels are WAY too faint to be really noticeable. :-s

14684322.review:
Es ist ein tolles logikspiel! Das Prinzip ist ähnlich wie Minesweeper, aber die zusätzlichen Elemente verhindern sehr, dass man gezwungen wird an manchen stellen zu raten. Zudem ist das Spiel nicht gleich vorbei, wenn man mal falsch lag -> Es gibt am Ende lediglich evt. Punktabzug dafür. 

Es gibt unterschiedliche zusätzliche Elemente:
- Alle blauen Flächen liegen 100% aneinander gereiht; 
- Es ist zu 100% eine Lücke in der blauen Reihe; 
- In der Reihe sind X blaue Flächen;
...

Ich finde, dass die zusätzlichen Elemente des Spiels es leichter machen, als Minesweeper (für die, die es vergleichen wollen), es jedoch auch umfangreicher und damit spaßiger ist als Zeitvertreib.

Zudem beinhaltet das Spiel 3 Teile, die glaub rund 25 Level enthalten. Für einen Teil braucht man rund 2 Stunden. Wobei sich in jedem Teil leider alle Level wiederholen... Es lohnt also nur, einen der drei Teile zu spielen.

Für Achievementjäger sei gesagt, dass hier nur der ein Teil relevant ist und man hierbei Fehler machen kann (!) sofern man am Ende alle Punkte für das Level bekommt.

